If invalid SQL is returned by the agent, and the user clicks the “execute SQL” button, they will get a SQLAlchemy error.
Add error handling to catch this error, and ultimately retry by prompting for a new SQL query from the agent.
“Whoops… I seem to have given you some invalid SQL. Let me run that again…”
Rerun chain (maybe with extra context? such as the error message, etc.)
